2. LIME MECHANICS — 4 SACRED STEPS
┌────────────────────┐
│ 1. PERTURB         │ ← Create 1,000 neighbors
│    (acres ±10%)    │
└───────┬────────────┘
        ▼
┌────────────────────┐
│ 2. PREDICT         │ ← Run black-box model
│    on all 1,000    │
└───────┬────────────┘
        ▼
┌────────────────────┐
│ 3. WEIGHT          │ ← Closer = higher weight
│    π(x) = e^(-d²)  │
└───────┬────────────┘
        ▼
┌────────────────────┐
│ 4. FIT SIMPLE      │ ← Linear model / Decision tree
│    g(z) ≈ f(x)     │
└───────┬────────────┘
        ▼
┌────────────────────┐
│ LIME EXPLANATION   │ ← "acres > 5000 → +0.92"
└────────────────────┘
3. MATHEMATICAL FLAME — LIME OPTIMIZATION
\[
\text{explanation}(x) = \arg\min_g L(f, g, \pi_x) + \Omega(g)
\]

Term

\( L \)
Local fidelity — how well \( g \) matches \( f \) near \( x \)
\( \pi_x(z) \)
Proximity kernel — \( e^{-d(x,z)^2 / \sigma^2} \)
\( \Omega(g) \)
Complexity penalty — keep \( g \) simple
